          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Measurements of  reaction 16O(g,n),  made with tagged",
                " photons at  Eg  near 58 MeV,  are presented.  Neutron",
                " energy determination was  made  by  time  of  flight,",
                " giving a  resolution of about 2 MeV which enabled the",
                " ground-state excitation  in 15O to be  resolved  from",
                " states at   5.2   and  6.2  MeV.  Differential  cross",
                " sections were measured in the angular range 30 -  110",
                " deg and   are   compared   with  the  predictions  of",
                " microscopic, self-consistent   Hartree-Fock,   random",
                " phase approximation  model  of  (g,n) reactions.  The",
                " implications for  the  theoretical  description   are",
                " discussed, notably  the dependence of the (g,n) cross",
                " section on meson exchange  currents  and  final-state",
                " rescattering."
              ]
            }
          ],
